lant Committee, an all black organization that helped escaped slaves secure passage to the North, the New York Times described Purvis at the time of his death as the president of the Underground Railroad. Voicing his opposition to a decision by the state of Pennsylvania to disenfranchise black voters in 1838, Purvis declared "there is but one race, the human race." But One Race is the dramatic story of one of the most important figures of his time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAbolitionistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aAfrican American abolitionistsvBiography. 0aAfrican American civil rights workersvBiography. 0aAfrican AmericanszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiavBiography. 0aAntislavery movementszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy19th century. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHistory : American History. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791480427423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791480427/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles